
Podcast of the MIT, via https://open.spotify.com/show/43Sy07hx8cZSppbKBin5s0


=Description=

Vasilis Kostakis:

"We discuss how commons-based energy systems differ from traditional models and examine how community control and sufficiency principles might break the rebound effect. We discuss the "design global, manufacture local" approach and its applications to energy infrastructure. The conversation also addresses contextual differences in post-growth discussions between Europe & the US, and considers how AI might contribute to commons-based energy systems."


